- The global light attack and reconnaissance aircraft market is segmented based on the type of aircraft, distinguishing between fixed-wing aircraft and rotary-wing aircraft. Fixed-wing aircraft offer advantages such as longer endurance and higher speed, making them suitable for certain missions, while rotary-wing aircraft provide versatility in terms of take-off and landing capabilities, crucial for operations in confined areas.

